        static void fillInventory​(int bagsNum)

      • search

        static void search​(long count,
                   boolean isLinear)
        Search (with option to choose linear or binary approach and number of times) randomly choose item from origin itemsLinkedList by name and rarity. Note: in case if there was a chosen binarySearch, This can't guarantee good results because of the inventory sorted by name but we need to find item which will be same per name and rarity
        Parameters:
        count - repeats count for search
        isLinear - in case true will be use linearSearch, otherwise binarySearch

      • sortByName

        static void sortByName​(int fromIndex,
                       int toIndex)
        Sorts inventory from index fromIndex, inclusive, to index toIndex, exclusive, by name using default java sort function which provides stable merge sort, guarantees complexity O(n log n) in worst case.
        Parameters:
        fromIndex - index of first element (inclusive)
        toIndex - index of last element (exclusive)

      • sortByCurrentStrength

        static void sortByCurrentStrength​(int fromIndex,
                                  int toIndex)
        Sorts inventory on range from index fromIndex, inclusive, to index toIndex, exclusive with same names by currentStrength. Approach: compare current itemName with next if names are different calls sort method and sort on range startIndex to i+1. To avoid situation when last item has same name as previous when i == toIndex-2 sort range from startIndex, inclusive, to toIndex, exclusive.
        Parameters:
        fromIndex - index of first element (inclusive)
        toIndex - index of last element (exclusive)

      • multiMergeSort

        static void multiMergeSort()
        At the beginning creates new inventory. Sorts each bag separately be name then by each name subgroup by currentStrength then sort whole inventory at time.
